      "10",
      "11",
      "12"
    ],
    "ecommerce_buffer_pairs": 40,
    "time_horizon_days": 14,
    "notes": "Use up to the store labor transfer cap (320 pairs) this week. Allocate approximately 80% of transferable pairs to mountain stores with recent >19% conversion uplift after rain; reserve ~40 pairs as fast-turn ecommerce fulfillment buffer for sizes 10-12 to reduce lost sales while transfers complete."
  },
  "rationale": "Mountain stores show a clear short-term demand spike (conversion +19% after rain) and have experienced 5-day stockouts in sizes 10-12, indicating unmet demand and potential lost sales. Vendor lead time (6 weeks) prevents immediate replenishment from new production, and e-commerce returns (16% for fit) reduce reliable inbound replenishment. Store labor is the binding operational constraint (cap 320 transfers), so reallocating existing inventory to where conversion is highest is the fastest way to capture incremental sales. A small ecommerce buffer reduces immediate online loss while transfers are processed. This minimizes downside risk while respecting operational limits and avoids speculative ordering.",
